<quiz>
  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Factorising a quadratic expression using the difference of squares identity</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Factorise the following expression completely:
\[
{@expr@}
\]
</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Here we use the identity:
</p>

<p>
\[
a^2 - b^2 = (a-b)(a+b)
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the two square terms.
</p>

<p>
\[
{@expr@}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
{@A@}x^2 = ({@a@}x)^2
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
{@B@} = {@b@}^2
\]
</p>

<p>
So the expression has the form:
</p>

<p>
\[
({@a@}x)^2 - {@b@}^2
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Apply the difference of squares identity.
</p>

<p>
\[
({@a@}x)^2 - {@b@}^2 =
({@a@}x - {@b@})({@a@}x + {@b@})
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the factorised form is:
</p>

<p>
\[
({@a@}x - {@b@})({@a@}x + {@b@})
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
